com.phunware.mapping.manager

Class PhunwareMapManager

  • com.phunware.mapping.manager.PhunwareMapManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LocationDebugInfoReceiver.DebugInfoListener

    public class PhunwareMapManager
implements LocationDebugInfoReceiver.DebugInfoListener

    Allows interaction with Phunware's mapping service to easily manage building data on a PhunwareMap, and provides navigation abilities using the supplied metadata.

    The PhunwareMapManager should generally be an application level singleton, and can be initialized automatically by calling PhunwareMapManager.create.

    To override the mapping server endpoint, to test against the staging environment, for instance, add a metadata entry to your application's manifest with the name phunware-mapping-endpoint.

      Enables Managed compass Managed compass is disabled by default Managed compass is an optional capability of the Location SDK that improves the user experience while viewing the map by improving the alignment of the compass heading. The managed compass takes operating system readings and processes them prior to returning it to the Location SDK - so there is no further coding required for developers once using this mode.
